abstract: Bernard Madoff's former customers will soon see their total recovery approach $14 billion, a court-appointed trustee said on Friday, as the dying swindler awaits a decision on whether the U.S. government will support his request to leave prison early.
snippet: Bernard Madoff's former customers will soon see their total recovery approach $14 billion, a court-appointed trustee said on Friday, as the dying swindler awaits a decision on whether the U.S. government will support his request to leave prison ea...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Bernard Madoff's former customers will soon see their total recovery approach $14 billion, a court-appointed trustee said on Friday, as the dying swindler awaits a decision on whether the U.S. government will support his request to leave prison early.
headline_main: Madoff Customer Payout Nears $14 Billion, as Dying Swindler Seeks Freedom
headline_print_headline: Madoff Customer Payout Nears $14 Billion, as Dying Swindler Seeks Freedom

abstract: An Alabama man arrested for slashing a towering protest balloon depicting President Donald Trump as a baby was ordered to attend counseling and complete community service for a chance at getting the charges dismissed.
snippet: An Alabama man arrested for slashing a towering protest balloon depicting President Donald Trump as a baby was ordered to attend counseling and complete community service for a chance at getting the charges dismissed.
lead_paragraph: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. — An Alabama man arrested for slashing a towering protest balloon depicting President Donald Trump as a baby was ordered to attend counseling and complete community service for a chance at getting the charges dismissed.
headline_main: Man Ordered Into Diversion for Popping 'Baby Trump' Balloon
headline_print_headline: Man Ordered Into Diversion for Popping 'Baby Trump' Balloon

abstract: America has always known haves and have-nots. But what was a tiered system is morphing into a caste system.
snippet: America has always known haves and have-nots. But what was a tiered system is morphing into a caste system.
lead_paragraph: A $1,000 seat at Yankee Stadium, in the first few rows along the baseline, is known as a Legends ticket. Holders bypass the long lines of fans waiting to enter the park by conventional means, whisked in by security guards who greet them like family. They enjoy a private dining room and concierge access, and they are separated from lesser fans by a concrete moat.

abstract: The federal jail in New York City where wealthy financier Jeffrey Epstein took his own life is on lockdown as authorities try to determine whether someone smuggled a gun inside one of the most secure federal jails in the country, three people familiar with the matter told The Associated Press.
snippet: The federal jail in New York City where wealthy financier Jeffrey Epstein took his own life is on lockdown as authorities try to determine whether someone smuggled a gun inside one of the most secure federal jails in the country, three people fami...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal jail in New York City where wealthy financier Jeffrey Epstein took his own life is on lockdown as authorities try to determine whether someone smuggled a gun inside one of the most secure federal jails in the country, three people familiar with the matter told The Associated Press.
headline_main: AP Sources: Feds Search for Possible Gun at Epstein Jail
headline_print_headline: AP Sources: Feds Search for Possible Gun at Epstein Jail

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo defended the Trump administration's response to the spreading coronavirus but also faced contentious questions Friday from Democrats about the basis for an airstrike that killed Iran's most powerful general and whether the attack had put American security at risk.
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo defended the Trump administration's response to the spreading coronavirus but also faced contentious questions Friday from Democrats about the basis for an airstrike that killed Iran's most powerful general and wheth...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo defended the Trump administration's response to the spreading coronavirus but also faced contentious questions Friday from Democrats about the basis for an airstrike that killed Iran's most powerful general and whether the attack had put American security at risk.
headline_main: Dems Joust With Pompeo at Hearing, the 1st Since Impeachment
headline_print_headline: Dems Joust With Pompeo at Hearing, the 1st Since Impeachment

abstract: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo will witness the signing of a U.S.-Taliban agreement on a withdrawal of American troops from Afghanistan, President Donald Trump said on Friday, heralding an agreement that could help his re-election campaign.
snippet: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo will witness the signing of a U.S.-Taliban agreement on a withdrawal of American troops from Afghanistan, President Donald Trump said on Friday, heralding an agreement that could help his re-election campaign.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo will witness the signing of a U.S.-Taliban agreement on a withdrawal of American troops from Afghanistan, President Donald Trump said on Friday, heralding an agreement that could help his re-election campaign.
headline_main: Pompeo to Attend Signing of U.S.-Taliban Troop Withdrawal Pact
headline_print_headline: Pompeo to Attend Signing of U.S.-Taliban Troop Withdrawal Pact

abstract: The Judiciary Committee requested records and interviews with prosecutors related to possible “improper political interference” at the department.
snippet: The Judiciary Committee requested records and interviews with prosecutors related to possible “improper political interference” at the department.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats are scrutinizing whether President Trump or his appointees have interfered at the Justice Department for political reasons, a committee chairman said Friday, requesting documents and interviews with 15 U.S. attorneys related to the cases of three Trump associates and a review of the F.B.I.’s Russia inquiry.

headline_main: House Democrats Inquire About Political Interference at the Justice Dept.
headline_print_headline: House Starts Inquiry on Political Meddling at Justice

abstract: The House Judiciary Committee is launching a wide-ranging probe of Attorney General William Barr and the Justice Department, demanding briefings, documents and interviews with 15 officials as it tries to determine whether there has been improper political interference in federal law enforcement.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House Judiciary Committee is launching a wide-ranging probe of Attorney General William Barr and the Justice Department, demanding briefings, documents and interviews with 15 officials as it tries to determine whether there has been improper political interference in federal law enforcement.
